cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata theory and regular languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper analyzes the space complexity of streaming algorithms. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the concept of language growth. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the paper deals with the decision problem of whether a language can be recognized by a sliding window algorithm. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper establishes tight relationships between space complexity and automata size.
